1
00:00:01,900 --> 00:00:04,570
Episode 7

2
00:00:04,570 --> 00:00:09,710
Let's ride the cable car tomorrow morning.

3
00:00:34,190 --> 00:00:39,540
Who killed your brother?

4
00:00:39,540 --> 00:00:41,980
Someone he loved.

5
00:00:41,980 --> 00:00:43,870
May I...

6
00:00:45,270 --> 00:00:48,850
ask for your brother's name?

7
00:00:52,120 --> 00:00:58,700
Ian. Kim Ian.

8
00:01:02,470 --> 00:01:05,440
Do you know him?

9
00:01:06,830 --> 00:01:12,110
No. I'm hearing it for the first time. What does he do?

10
00:01:18,490 --> 00:01:22,920
- Don't move.
- No, I'm alright.

11
00:01:25,180 --> 00:01:27,930
I told you not to move.

12
00:01:39,190 --> 00:01:46,630
Saying someone was murdered by the one he loved is not a joke. What exactly does that mean?

13
00:01:47,320 --> 00:01:49,340
What?

14
00:01:50,520 --> 00:01:53,480
No, it's nothing.

15
00:01:54,730 --> 00:01:58,070
Try getting up.

16
00:01:59,380 --> 00:02:01,380
Do you think you can walk?

17
00:02:02,330 --> 00:02:08,970
Yes. It doesn't hurt that much either.

18
00:02:08,970 --> 00:02:13,350
You're so relaxed. Can you laugh at a time like this?

19
00:02:30,680 --> 00:02:34,450
You said you couldn't eat nor drive because your hand hurt.

20
00:02:34,450 --> 00:02:36,970
Have you seen a lunar eclipse before?

21
00:02:36,970 --> 00:02:40,680
Lunar eclipse? Maybe a few times on TV.

22
00:02:40,680 --> 00:02:45,310
Watching it on TV is not the real thing.

23
00:02:55,500 --> 00:02:59,170
There's a real shadow on the moon.

24
00:02:59,170 --> 00:03:04,660
This is my first time seeing it this close. This is so fascinating...

25
00:03:04,660 --> 00:03:08,350
The black part that hides the moon is the earth's shadow right?

26
00:03:08,350 --> 00:03:15,370
It's a partial lunar eclipse.  The moon will be half-covered.

27
00:03:18,040 --> 00:03:22,730
- Do you come here a lot to see the moon?
- I used to come often.

28
00:03:23,340 --> 00:03:26,790
My little brother liked it.

29
00:03:26,790 --> 00:03:30,600
Who killed your brother?

30
00:03:30,600 --> 00:03:33,280
Someone he loved.

31
00:03:35,760 --> 00:03:44,250
Hey...um... this has been continuously on my mind since earlier...

32
00:03:44,250 --> 00:03:48,890
About your little brother... May I ask what happened?

33
00:03:51,190 --> 00:03:56,640
If you don't want to tell me, you don't have to tell.

34
00:03:56,640 --> 00:04:04,150
It was an accident. A car crash. That's what my father told me.

35
00:04:04,150 --> 00:04:06,610
Oh, that's what it was.

36
00:04:07,480 --> 00:04:12,370
His girlfriend must have been driving.

37
00:04:12,370 --> 00:04:15,250
What happened to his girlfriend?

38
00:04:16,360 --> 00:04:22,950
- She's alive and well.
- Goodness. In the midst of misfortune, she was lucky.

39
00:04:28,760 --> 00:04:35,040
Actually, I was in a car accident last summer.

40
00:04:36,340 --> 00:04:38,560
What kind of accident?

41
00:04:44,130 --> 00:04:48,040
According to my unni, it was a taxi accident.

42
00:04:49,590 --> 00:04:53,940
Truthfully, I don't remember anything about it.

43
00:04:53,940 --> 00:04:58,890
I lost all memory for the three months before  and after the accident.

44
00:04:58,890 --> 00:05:05,530
Unni explained it using complex words.  Short Term Dissociative  Amnesia?

45
00:05:05,530 --> 00:05:11,840
Do you remember whom you killed?

46
00:05:11,840 --> 00:05:15,150
You don't remember anything of these three months.

47
00:05:16,250 --> 00:05:18,810
Is that possible?

48
00:05:19,790 --> 00:05:22,690
Well, that's what actually happened.

49
00:05:22,690 --> 00:05:30,390
I also only thought that could only happen in movies, but I learned that it happens in real life too.

50
00:05:35,540 --> 00:05:38,030
Don't you want to know?

51
00:05:39,780 --> 00:05:47,960
What's inside the memory that you lost. Don't you want to know?

52
00:05:50,140 --> 00:05:56,830
Uhm, I'm not sure. I don't know.

53
00:05:56,830 --> 00:06:04,520
I both want to know and am afraid.

54
00:06:04,520 --> 00:06:12,110
I have nightmares sometimes and I think, what if they are my memories?

55
00:06:20,250 --> 00:06:24,880
Let's stop talking about this. I'm getting bored.

56
00:06:24,880 --> 00:06:27,730
Let's go in now.

57
00:06:35,150 --> 00:06:38,010
Why a duet all of sudden?

58
00:06:38,010 --> 00:06:43,340
You're not playing the piano right?

59
00:06:43,340 --> 00:06:47,850
- It's a duet. Let's play together.
- Huh?

60
00:06:47,850 --> 00:06:53,570
You hurt your hand too.What do you mean you're going to play. I haven't played in a long time too.

61
00:06:53,570 --> 00:06:58,250
When I was young, I studied the piano for maybe three years.

62
00:07:00,410 --> 00:07:04,860
You said your little brother was a pianist, right?

63
00:07:08,350 --> 00:07:12,410
- When you were young, you must've played together often.
- Not often but sometimes.

64
00:07:12,410 --> 00:07:18,650
We didn't live together, so we only met during the holidays. When we met,  we often came here.

65
00:07:23,140 --> 00:07:26,240
This would be good.

66
00:07:27,190 --> 00:07:30,380
Debussy would be nice, right?

67
00:07:37,840 --> 00:07:41,490
It's my hand when I was younger.

68
00:07:41,490 --> 00:07:45,150
Was it during the summer vacation of 6th grade?

69
00:07:45,150 --> 00:07:50,960
My brother would often cry when he practiced at night because he was scared.

70
00:07:52,110 --> 00:07:54,860
I drew it then.

71
00:08:11,830 --> 00:08:15,910
Like this, I put my hand there.

72
00:08:22,120 --> 00:08:27,760
Now, look, do it like that.

73
00:08:27,760 --> 00:08:32,890
It looks as if you're holding your hyung's hand. So, you don't have to be scared.

74
00:08:32,890 --> 00:08:40,060
Because you and I are here together.

75
00:08:51,390 --> 00:08:53,830
I'm sorry.

76
00:08:55,280 --> 00:08:57,580
What's wrong with me?

77
00:08:59,200 --> 00:09:02,650
I don't think I'm in my right mind.

78
00:09:07,410 --> 00:09:14,620
Maybe it's because you told me before that your brother was in an accident.

79
00:09:17,100 --> 00:09:20,120
Let's go now. It's getting late.

80
00:09:20,120 --> 00:09:26,350
I'm very busy after becoming the conductor's assistant. My work time starts earlier too.

81
00:09:26,350 --> 00:09:32,370
Why? Why do you keep running away, huh?

82
00:09:32,370 --> 00:09:37,010
Why do you keep running away? I want to know more.

83
00:09:38,040 --> 00:09:45,710
You keep running away and I don't know what to do.

84
00:09:47,750 --> 00:09:51,410
I want to know more about you.

85
00:09:52,430 --> 00:09:58,620
The more the better. I want to know what others don't know.

86
00:09:59,690 --> 00:10:02,960
I wish you stopped doing that.

87
00:10:05,290 --> 00:10:08,220
Let's just go today.

88
00:10:28,170 --> 00:10:33,450
I want to know you more. The more the better.

89
00:10:41,030 --> 00:10:44,390
What? Do you have something to say?

90
00:10:45,770 --> 00:10:52,020
You know... the thing you said to me before...

91
00:10:58,290 --> 00:11:02,620
Never mind. It's nothing.

92
00:11:02,620 --> 00:11:11,000
Timing and Subtitles by the Sing To Me Team @ viki

93
00:11:19,490 --> 00:11:21,510
Jang Yun's brother...

94
00:11:21,510 --> 00:11:25,140
May I ask  your brother's name?

95
00:11:25,140 --> 00:11:28,110
Ian.

96
00:11:28,110 --> 00:11:30,370
Kim Ian.

97
00:11:30,370 --> 00:11:33,780
Why does it sound so familiar?

98
00:11:33,780 --> 00:11:37,410
Those two... why do they have different surnames?

99
00:11:47,890 --> 00:11:49,810
Short-term Dissociative Amnesia?

100
00:11:49,810 --> 00:11:52,220
I can't remember what happened before the accident.

101
00:11:52,220 --> 00:11:55,460
I can't remember anything of the three months before and after the accident.

102
00:11:55,460 --> 00:11:57,980
I don't know.

103
00:11:57,980 --> 00:12:00,250
I don't remember.

104
00:12:00,250 --> 00:12:03,110
She can't remember anything. Is that even possible?

105
00:12:03,110 --> 00:12:05,550
Well, that's what actually happened.

106
00:12:23,270 --> 00:12:25,090
Yes.

107
00:12:26,450 --> 00:12:28,210
Don't think about it, alright? Don't think about it.

108
00:12:28,210 --> 00:12:30,350
You can't think anymore.

109
00:12:35,030 --> 00:12:36,550
I must be crazy.

110
00:12:36,550 --> 00:12:38,750
What do I do?

111
00:12:41,700 --> 00:12:46,160
Weirdly, that woman doesn't remember anything before the accident.

112
00:12:46,160 --> 00:12:49,610
She doesn't know who Ian is, nor does she know that he died.

113
00:12:49,610 --> 00:12:52,170
And the hospital records confirm this.

114
00:12:52,170 --> 00:12:54,990
I think we have to move in a different direction.

115
00:13:12,740 --> 00:13:18,140
I Wanna Hear Your Song

116
00:13:18,140 --> 00:13:21,020
Yes, we have a meeting with the Chairwoman at 11.00.

117
00:13:21,020 --> 00:13:23,010
There's a luncheon at noon with the Orchestra Supporters' Association.

118
00:13:23,010 --> 00:13:26,940
The sample poster for the inaugural concert will be available at 4 pm.

119
00:13:26,940 --> 00:13:29,980
By the way, do you know Conductor Song arrives from Germany today?

120
00:13:29,980 --> 00:13:33,370
There will be a homecoming celebration at his home at 7 pm tomorrow.

121
00:13:33,400 --> 00:13:36,300
You need to attend.
Phone me.

122
00:13:36,300 --> 00:13:39,900
I'm going to the salon to pick up the Chairwoman.

123
00:13:39,900 --> 00:13:41,510
Yes.

124
00:13:44,700 --> 00:13:47,210
I'll meet you at O-Chan.

125
00:13:49,130 --> 00:13:50,610
Yes?

126
00:13:50,610 --> 00:13:52,940
Oh, Assistant Yang. Why?

127
00:13:54,150 --> 00:13:55,660
What?

128
00:13:55,660 --> 00:13:58,390
Wait... what?

129
00:14:04,560 --> 00:14:06,290
Why, what's happening?

130
00:14:06,290 --> 00:14:09,610
He's telling us to come out, we're doing the rehearsal outdoors.

131
00:14:09,610 --> 00:14:10,260
What?

132
00:14:10,260 --> 00:14:12,760
It's Maestro Nam's decision.

133
00:14:28,430 --> 00:14:30,140
My instrument is going to get warped.

134
00:14:30,140 --> 00:14:31,650
Are we seriously going to rehearse here?

135
00:14:31,650 --> 00:14:34,050
What are we supposed to do?

136
00:14:34,050 --> 00:14:35,720
All the instruments are going to get warped.

137
00:14:35,720 --> 00:14:37,890
Maestro Nam is a complete dictator.

138
00:14:37,890 --> 00:14:39,130
I know, right?!

139
00:14:39,130 --> 00:14:40,560
He's really doing all sorts of things.

140
00:14:40,560 --> 00:14:43,720
The kids of no consequence are to blame.

141
00:14:43,720 --> 00:14:45,400
What? Look here.

142
00:14:45,400 --> 00:14:48,590
What did you say?

143
00:14:48,590 --> 00:14:52,370
In the time you're cussing out the conductor, practice.

144
00:14:52,370 --> 00:14:55,490
Your performance is killing me.

145
00:14:55,490 --> 00:14:58,250
Good morning, everyone!

146
00:15:00,820 --> 00:15:03,030
The weather is amazing today, right?

147
00:15:03,030 --> 00:15:04,630
Yes.

148
00:15:04,630 --> 00:15:08,380
Look, there's the sky.

149
00:15:10,140 --> 00:15:12,350
It's so blue.

150
00:15:15,620 --> 00:15:20,840
The conductor must be crazy, he's making such a commotion to play outdoors. You guys badmouthed me a lot, right?

151
00:15:20,840 --> 00:15:22,940
Yes.

152
00:15:22,940 --> 00:15:24,600
I don't have a specific reason.

153
00:15:24,600 --> 00:15:28,350
Just because there's land here, trees here,

154
00:15:28,350 --> 00:15:30,880
a sky on top of us, and a breeze is blowing.

155
00:15:30,880 --> 00:15:34,420
We will just play The Thousand and One Nights.

156
00:15:34,420 --> 00:15:37,470
It's great we're doing music, right?

157
00:15:37,470 --> 00:15:39,870
Yes.

158
00:15:39,870 --> 00:15:41,440
It might be better indoors,

159
00:15:41,440 --> 00:15:45,790
but pretend this is an Arabian palace of the night and play.

160
00:15:45,790 --> 00:15:50,840
Rimsky-Korsakov's "Scheherazade", second movement.

161
00:16:31,880 --> 00:16:34,290
Manager Yun!

162
00:16:39,240 --> 00:16:41,610
Occupied

163
00:17:08,070 --> 00:17:10,260
Where are all the musicians?

164
00:17:10,260 --> 00:17:15,710
Ou-ou-outdoors, on an empty lot.

165
00:18:15,560 --> 00:18:18,320
Hong Yi Yeong.

166
00:18:18,320 --> 00:18:22,180
Keep filming what you're filming and don't look at me.

167
00:18:22,180 --> 00:18:23,090
Oh, yes.

168
00:18:23,090 --> 00:18:26,330
Do you know what our orchestra's annual budget is?

169
00:18:26,330 --> 00:18:27,920
No, not really.

170
00:18:27,920 --> 00:18:33,620
Every year, to obtain that money, I have to throw away my pride and do so many despicable—

171
00:18:36,070 --> 00:18:38,860
You were an orchestra member once, so you're well aware.

172
00:18:38,860 --> 00:18:42,110
Who will reimburse for  instruments that may get damaged outside?

173
00:18:42,110 --> 00:18:46,290
I ask again, who will pay if the members need to be reimbursed?

174
00:18:46,290 --> 00:18:47,000
That is...

175
00:18:47,000 --> 00:18:50,290
Do you feel wronged and wonder, who the heck is this woman to tell me this?

176
00:18:50,290 --> 00:18:50,930
No, I—

177
00:18:50,930 --> 00:18:53,730
If you were the best performer, you need to act accordingly,

178
00:18:53,730 --> 00:18:57,220
by knowing this would happen and stopping it.

179
00:18:57,220 --> 00:19:00,520
I signed your contract so you can do work like this.

180
00:19:00,520 --> 00:19:03,250
You need to stop the conductor from doing psychotic things.

181
00:19:03,250 --> 00:19:05,960
We're paying you with our precious budget.

182
00:19:05,960 --> 00:19:07,890
Do you understand?

183
00:19:09,140 --> 00:19:12,420
I'm sorry, I'm sorry.

184
00:19:12,420 --> 00:19:17,720
Please stop apologizing, I don't like receiving apologies. Just stop creating problems that will make you apologize.

185
00:19:21,310 --> 00:19:22,630
This is my number.

186
00:19:22,630 --> 00:19:26,660
Send me the performance video so I can send it to the orchestra supporters.

187
00:20:17,990 --> 00:20:20,790
Good work, everyone.

188
00:20:20,790 --> 00:20:22,730
Great job, great job.

189
00:20:22,730 --> 00:20:26,380
You did well, you did well.

190
00:20:26,380 --> 00:20:28,520
You did well.

191
00:20:47,310 --> 00:20:49,760
Where are you going?

192
00:20:49,760 --> 00:20:51,440
Father, be quiet.

193
00:20:51,440 --> 00:20:54,390
I'm going to go to the hospital right now.

194
00:20:54,390 --> 00:20:56,110
I heard you're off today.

195
00:20:56,110 --> 00:20:57,600
Father, shhhh.

196
00:20:57,600 --> 00:21:00,500
Please be quiet, my mom will hear.

197
00:21:00,500 --> 00:21:03,530
When my mom looks for me, pretend I was never here.

198
00:21:03,530 --> 00:21:05,350
You got it, right?

199
00:21:10,390 --> 00:21:12,570
I see you think very simplistically.

200
00:21:12,570 --> 00:21:15,390
Shall I sell the family register this instant?

201
00:21:22,190 --> 00:21:24,360
You!

202
00:21:29,050 --> 00:21:31,140
You seriously...

203
00:21:48,520 --> 00:21:51,640
Why is this person not coming?

204
00:22:05,180 --> 00:22:07,230
Miss Hong Su Yeong?

205
00:22:08,230 --> 00:22:10,900
Yes, and...?

206
00:22:10,900 --> 00:22:12,690
I'm Choi Gi Sang.

207
00:22:12,690 --> 00:22:14,630
I got it.

208
00:22:21,560 --> 00:22:24,470
I'm dressed like this because I came here in a rush.

209
00:22:24,470 --> 00:22:25,490
I apologize.

210
00:22:25,490 --> 00:22:29,290
I don't really care about what you're wearing.

211
00:22:29,290 --> 00:22:31,620
The person I was going to meet is Lee Gyeong Su.

212
00:22:31,620 --> 00:22:33,650
Lawyer Lee Gyeong Su.

213
00:22:33,650 --> 00:22:35,670
Lee Gyeong Su can't come out today.

214
00:22:35,670 --> 00:22:37,990
- Why?
- Something came up.

215
00:22:37,990 --> 00:22:41,150
Something came up? Could he not have told me beforehand?

216
00:22:41,150 --> 00:22:43,090
Then who are you?

217
00:22:43,090 --> 00:22:44,520
No, wait, I don't need to know.

218
00:22:44,520 --> 00:22:46,940
Okay, I got it.

219
00:22:46,940 --> 00:22:49,320
Are you, perhaps, hungry?

220
00:22:49,320 --> 00:22:52,360
My stomach? I'm hungry, of course, it's past my mealtime.

221
00:22:52,360 --> 00:22:54,710
Let's go out together.

222
00:23:03,370 --> 00:23:04,830
What are you looking at?

223
00:23:04,830 --> 00:23:09,520
I rode my motorcycle today, but you can't ride one, so let's call a taxi.

224
00:23:10,840 --> 00:23:12,630
Wait a second. Hey!

225
00:23:12,630 --> 00:23:15,150
Wait a minute, let's go together!

226
00:23:21,260 --> 00:23:22,760
Are you alright?

227
00:23:22,760 --> 00:23:24,890
I'm so embarrassed.

228
00:23:37,070 --> 00:23:41,340
Hi, did you lose anything? Do you need any help?

229
00:23:41,340 --> 00:23:45,810
I dropped my reed and I can't find it. I can find it myself, you go on.

230
00:23:45,810 --> 00:23:47,130
I can help you look for it.

231
00:23:47,130 --> 00:23:50,710
I said it's fine. If I find it, I want to be the one to find it.

232
00:23:50,710 --> 00:23:52,290
It's faster than finding it yourself though.

233
00:23:52,290 --> 00:23:54,250
I'll help.

234
00:24:05,390 --> 00:24:06,910
I found it.

235
00:24:06,910 --> 00:24:09,260
Here you go.

236
00:24:09,260 --> 00:24:11,090
I said that I would find it.

237
00:24:11,090 --> 00:24:13,870
I don't like it when other people touch my reed.

238
00:24:13,870 --> 00:24:16,620
As a fellow musician, can you not tell?

239
00:24:16,620 --> 00:24:20,060
Or rather, are you not a musician anymore?

240
00:24:22,330 --> 00:24:24,560
I'm sorry.

241
00:24:25,370 --> 00:24:29,850
This may be hard to hear but I was able to come this far with talent and effort.

242
00:24:29,850 --> 00:24:31,660
And this is true for most orchestra members here.

243
00:24:31,660 --> 00:24:35,160
I hope you'll be able to do this too, one day.

244
00:24:48,030 --> 00:24:50,350
That's done.

245
00:24:50,350 --> 00:24:52,750
That's also done.

246
00:24:52,750 --> 00:24:57,990
This may be hard to hear, but I was able to come this far with talent and effort.

247
00:24:57,990 --> 00:25:01,510
I hope you'll be able to do this too, one day.

248
00:25:02,990 --> 00:25:08,240
I put in the effort too. Effort and tears.

249
00:25:09,950 --> 00:25:13,060
Since the age of twelve, for fifteen years.

250
00:25:13,910 --> 00:25:18,760
Even when it rained, even when it snowed,

251
00:25:18,760 --> 00:25:20,900
even when I was sick,

252
00:25:26,670 --> 00:25:29,760
for 365 days, not a day less.

253
00:25:33,050 --> 00:25:38,170
Sundays, holidays,

254
00:25:38,170 --> 00:25:40,620
until the end,

255
00:25:41,660 --> 00:25:45,580
I stuck with it.

256
00:26:19,390 --> 00:26:23,070
Can I speak with you for one second?

257
00:26:26,480 --> 00:26:28,160
With me?

258
00:26:31,680 --> 00:26:32,590
What is it?

259
00:26:32,590 --> 00:26:34,970
If you perhaps have the time for a timpani lesson,

260
00:26:34,970 --> 00:26:37,830
can I ask you for some of your time?

261
00:26:39,230 --> 00:26:40,950
Lesson?

262
00:26:40,950 --> 00:26:45,160
You're not asking me for a lesson now, are you?

263
00:26:45,160 --> 00:26:47,080
Yes.

264
00:26:51,420 --> 00:26:55,610
I'm sorry, but I don't have any time.

265
00:27:00,840 --> 00:27:02,850
I'm leaving.

266
00:27:08,180 --> 00:27:12,150
Don't be like this. Please give me some time.

267
00:27:12,150 --> 00:27:15,270
It's alright even if it's one hour a week.

268
00:27:15,270 --> 00:27:16,640
Sorry.

269
00:27:16,640 --> 00:27:20,270
But... I really have no time.

270
00:27:22,640 --> 00:27:24,400
Good luck.

271
00:27:29,500 --> 00:27:33,230
It's no lie. He's highly sought-after.

272
00:27:33,230 --> 00:27:37,870
He's not trying to humiliate you. He really has no time.

273
00:27:37,870 --> 00:27:41,910
He doesn't seem nice but he's not a bad person.

274
00:28:03,530 --> 00:28:05,880
Are you done with your meeting?

275
00:28:07,520 --> 00:28:09,030
I barely escaped.

276
00:28:09,030 --> 00:28:13,160
If it went on for five more minutes, I'd hand in my resignation.

277
00:28:15,160 --> 00:28:17,090
What do you like?

278
00:28:17,090 --> 00:28:17,980
What?

279
00:28:17,980 --> 00:28:21,720
I'm going to give you a welcome dinner. Bring your stuff out.

280
00:28:50,690 --> 00:28:54,670
I remembered it right, you work here.

281
00:28:55,610 --> 00:28:58,870
You only stopped by briefly, still you remember. Thank you.

282
00:28:58,870 --> 00:29:01,270
We met here once before.

283
00:29:01,270 --> 00:29:03,720
He found my phone. Right?

284
00:29:03,720 --> 00:29:05,390
Yes.

285
00:29:06,530 --> 00:29:09,030
Today I'm giving a welcome dinner to Yi Yeong.

286
00:29:09,030 --> 00:29:12,230
While you were gone, she became my assistant.

287
00:29:12,230 --> 00:29:14,550
I heard.

288
00:29:14,550 --> 00:29:16,500
Congratulations.

289
00:29:17,810 --> 00:29:20,080
Congratulations? For what?

290
00:29:21,620 --> 00:29:26,700
How is your hand? Can you move it?

291
00:29:26,700 --> 00:29:29,290
It's almost healed.

292
00:29:33,170 --> 00:29:35,640
Did you sleep well yesterday?

293
00:29:36,610 --> 00:29:38,320
Yes?

294
00:29:39,200 --> 00:29:41,610
You were having a hard time sleeping.

295
00:29:41,610 --> 00:29:44,750
I was so worried then.

296
00:29:45,410 --> 00:29:47,510
Stop it.

297
00:29:47,510 --> 00:29:51,050
Yi Yeong, do you have trouble sleeping?

298
00:29:51,050 --> 00:29:54,280
No, I am sleeping very well these days.

299
00:29:54,280 --> 00:29:59,390
What do you mean you sleep well? You even ask me to sing a song to help you fall asleep.

300
00:30:00,990 --> 00:30:02,710
A song?

301
00:30:02,710 --> 00:30:04,760
Yes, a song.

302
00:30:04,760 --> 00:30:08,810
She says that she can sleep when someone sings.

303
00:30:09,660 --> 00:30:14,490
She begged me so much to sing for her.

304
00:30:15,470 --> 00:30:18,860
We have a relationship in which we help one another sleep.

305
00:30:18,860 --> 00:30:20,600
Stop!

306
00:30:26,980 --> 00:30:29,070
I'm going to the restroom.

307
00:30:40,670 --> 00:30:42,130
Are you crazy?

308
00:30:42,130 --> 00:30:45,980
What are you saying in front of the conductor? What do you mean by helping each other sleep?

309
00:30:45,980 --> 00:30:47,200
Why are you like this? I didn't say anything wrong.

310
00:30:47,200 --> 00:30:50,370
It is wrong. We don't help each other fall asleep.

311
00:30:50,370 --> 00:30:52,110
Please watch your mouth.

312
00:30:52,110 --> 00:30:53,610
Why should I?

313
00:30:53,610 --> 00:30:55,090
What do you mean why?

314
00:30:55,090 --> 00:30:57,710
It's not me that should be careful, but you.

315
00:30:57,710 --> 00:31:00,820
This is why there's a rumor that you slept with the conductor.

316
00:31:00,820 --> 00:31:03,430
Do you want to continue hearing that?

317
00:31:04,500 --> 00:31:07,140
Don't tell me... Did you actually sleep with him?

318
00:31:07,140 --> 00:31:08,540
What did you say?

319
00:31:08,540 --> 00:31:11,580
- That's an unfairly treated face.
- It wasn't fair. So then?

320
00:31:11,580 --> 00:31:14,320
Why are you like this to me?

321
00:31:21,550 --> 00:31:22,990
I don't have reason to feel good.

322
00:31:22,990 --> 00:31:26,010
The woman I'm interested in is eating with another guy.

323
00:31:26,010 --> 00:31:28,540
Especially a guy you have a rumor with.

324
00:31:30,270 --> 00:31:32,570
It's not that but...

325
00:31:32,570 --> 00:31:34,580
It's just a company dinner.  I told you it was a welcome celebration.

326
00:31:34,580 --> 00:31:37,090
It was just a welcome reception.

327
00:31:37,090 --> 00:31:39,170
Do you actually believe that?

328
00:31:41,250 --> 00:31:44,520
Are you naive or are you stupid?

329
00:31:46,520 --> 00:31:49,180
I won't bother you anymore.    Call me when you've decided what to order.
